The [[upper case]] form of the second [[letter]] of the modern [[w:Greek alphabet|Greek alphabet]], the [[lower case]] form is '''β'''. It is preceded by '''Α α''' and followed by '''Γ γ'''. 
==Translingual==
===Symbol===
'''Β''' 

# The upper case Greek letter [[beta]].

'''β'''
# The lower case Greek letter [[beta]].
# [[beta particle|β-particle]]: subatomic particle.
# Used in chemical nomenclature.

'''Β'''' or '''β''''
# The number two in [[w:Greek numerals|Greek numerals]].



